habitat: Creek bank. Grey-brown sandy loam. Land use: public/recreation.  Riparian area in disturbed, wet eucalypt forest. Associated species Eucalyptus tereticornis, E. grandis, Castanospermum australe, Aphananthe philippinensis, Cinnamomum camphora, Elaeocarpus grandis, Archontophoenix cunninghamiana.
locality: Nambour, at Showgrounds on Petrie Creek.
higherClassification: Plantae | Viridaeplantae | Streptophyta | Equisetopsida | Magnoliidae | Rosanae | Myrtales | Myrtaceae | Rhodamnia
eventRemarks: Slender tree, 12m; on riparian edge, multi-stemmed with shallowly tessellated bark, grey over tan. Leaves opposite, dark and glossy above, white and glaucous below; 3-veined at base with prominent intramarginal veins, veins strongly raised on underside. Fruit a globular berry ripening through red to black. Mostly 1 seeded. Rare at site. Common name: malletwood.
